/* 
This do file runs event study regressions on two main outcomes of interest: TransferSJVC ChangeSalaryGradeC.

    (1) However, I do not use each manager's true high-flyer status to construct the transition groups. 
    (2) I manually assign a manager with an odd ID as a high-flyer, and a manager with an even ID as a low-flyer. 
    (3) I then re-assign four event groups -- LtoL, LtoH, HtoH, and HtoL -- based on the manually assigned high-flyer status. 
    (4) I use the same time window for LtoL and LtoH groups, and the same time window for HtoH and HtoL groups. 
    (5) I do not include never-treated workers in the event study regressions. 

Notes on the event study regressions:
    (1) All four treatment groups are included (though Lto and Hto groups do not have same time window), while never-treated workers are not. 
    (2) The omitted group in the regressions are month -3, -2, and -1 for all four treatment groups.
    (3) For placebo LtoL and LtoH groups, the relative time period is [-36, +84], while for placebo HtoH and HtoL groups, the relative time period is [-36, +60].

Some key results (quarterly aggregated coefficients with their p-values, and other key summary statistics) are stored in the output file. 

Input: 
    "${TempData}/04MainOutcomesInEventStudies.dta" <== created in 0104 do file

Output:
    "${Results}/logfile_20250227_TwoMainOutcomesInEventStudies_Placebo.txt"

RA: WWZ 
Time: 2025-02-27
*/

